# Presence of this file declares: every commit in this repository must be signed.
#
# It is TRACKED in git on purpose. The requirement is a property of the repository,
# not of any one clone, so it must not be expressible as local git config that a
# fresh worktree can silently miss -- that is precisely how #2624 shipped an
# unsigned commit while `commit.gpgsign` looked correct everywhere else.
#
# Read by scripts/check-commit-signing.sh, which .githooks/pre-commit invokes.
# Deleting this file turns the local pre-commit check into a no-op. It does NOT
# relax the `required_signatures` ruleset on main, which lives on infrastructure
# the committer does not control and is what actually blocks the merge. The
# "Signed Commits" CI check also still runs, but it is not yet registered as a
# required context, so today it reports rather than blocks. See
# docs/dev-setup.md.
